GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 378
Short Title: Leon's Law (Dual Enrollment Info Parents). (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Pickett, Cotham, Liu, and Hawkins (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Higher Education, if favorable, Judiciary 3, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and
Operations of the House
March 13, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE EDUCATIONAL RECORDS OF MINOR COMMUNITY COLLEGE
3 STUDENTS TO THE PARENTS OF THE DEPENDENT STUDENT.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. This act shall be known and may be cited as "Leon's Law."
6 SECTION 2. Chapter 115D of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
7 Article to read:
8 "Article 10.
9 "Academic Records.
10 "§ 115D-110. Academic records of minor students.
11 (a) To the extent allowed under the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA),
12 20 U.S.C. § 1232g, each community college shall make educational records, as defined in 34
13 C.F.R. § 99.3, of minor students automatically available to the parents, guardians, or an
14 individual acting as a parent in the absence of a parent or a guardian of the student if the following
15 criteria are met:
16 (1) The student is below the age of 18.
17 (2) The student is a dependent student, as defined in section 152 of the Internal
18 Revenue Code of 1986.
19 (3) The parent has not opted out of receiving the records.
20 (b) Each community college shall require minor students whose educational records are
21 subject to subsection (a) of this section to complete a form, prior to registration in any course at
22 the community college, acknowledging that the parents, guardians, or an individual acting as a
23 parent in the absence of a parent or a guardian of the student has access to the educational records
24 of the student."
25 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies beginning with
26 the 2025-2026 academic year.
